      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched squeal when braking, sounds like a typical \"goblin's shriek\" - a warning sign that something's amiss. The fact that it's only coming from the front passenger side suggests a possible issue with the brake pads or rotors on that side. It's possible that the brake pads are worn down, causing the metal to vibrate and produce that squeal. You might want to check the brake pads and rotors for excessive wear or damage. \n\nIt's also worth noting that a worn-out brake pad can be a bit like a goblin's lair - it's hiding in plain sight, but if you don't address it, it can cause more problems down the line. I'd recommend having a mechanic take a look at your Camry's brakes to determine the cause of the squeal and recommend any necessary repairs.",
